This paper focuses on using NLP techniques such as word embeddings, tagging, and parsing to analyze historical syntax, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of ELMo embeddings, which are a type of deep learning model, suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the parsed data for accuracy in query searches suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and deep learning (cs.DL).
